Dec 9 2003	Staying at the Tria Hotel	The Tria Hotel was included as part of a hotel/air fare package offered by the travel agency I made arrangements with. Bear in mind that there are different types of hotels to accomodate the different needs of travelers. The Tria Hotel is designed for the budget conscious. Don't expect a porter to help bring your bags to your room or airport transportation. Yes, as a previous reviewer indicated, the rooms are small and are not designed for entertaining. If you do not like your room they will offer to place you in another room, if available. However, the hotel is very clean and there are two sitting areas within the lobby of the hotel for meeting friends. There are bus lines at the street corner and the nearest underground station is about three blocks away. The staff is very helpful although English is not their native language. As of November (when I stayed at the hotel), a comlimentary breakfast of cereal, toast, juice, coffee and tea is served daily in their breakfast room (they do not serve lunch or dinner). I have traveled for twenty years and have experienced all different types of hotels. All in all, I enjoyed my stay at the Trada.	
